---
description: Frontend architecture pattern — SvelteKit, feature folders mirroring backend modules, role-based route groups
globs: ["apps/web/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Reference: `ARCHITECTURE.md` Part 2. One SvelteKit app serves admin,
teacher, and parent — never separate apps per audience. Feature folders
mirror backend bounded contexts 1:1, the same vertical-slice philosophy as
the backend, not a type-based split (`components/`, `stores/`, `utils/` as
flat catch-alls holding everything).

- **A feature's `api.ts` is the only place that calls its corresponding
  backend module's endpoints.** If `outcomes` needs calendar data, import
  a function from `features/calendar/api.ts` — don't issue a raw fetch to
  `/calendar/...` from inside `outcomes/`. This is the frontend equivalent
  of "inject a service, never a repository."

- **Route groups (`(admin)/`, `(teacher)/`, `(parent)/`, `(auth)/`) are the
  role boundary, enforced in `+layout.ts` / `load` server-side** — never
  just a hidden nav link. Every route group needs its own role check that
  redirects/errors on mismatch, same discipline as the backend's
  `SubstituteRoleGuard`.

- **`lib/shared/` is for genuine design-system primitives only** (Button,
  Card, Modal, Badge, layout shell). A domain-specific component
  (`MilestoneSweepGrid`, `PacingBadge`) stays in its owning feature's
  `components/` folder even if it looks reusable — it doesn't move to
  `shared/` on that basis alone.

- **State stays light.** SvelteKit `load` functions for server-fetched
  data; small per-feature Svelte stores for client-only UI state. No
  global state library — cross-feature global state recreates the boundary
  violation the `api.ts` rule above exists to prevent.

- **The frontend is never the authority for access control.** It may
  disable/hide UI for a role that shouldn't use it, for UX — but every
  actual enforcement (two-grain scope, gravity rule, mapper guards) is
  backend-authoritative. Don't write client-side permission logic that
  duplicates (and could drift from) a backend guard.

- **`(parent)/` is view-only plus explicit confirm actions** (reply to a
  message, toggle photo consent) — don't add authoring/editing flows there
  beyond what the spec explicitly grants parents.

- **Type drift:** import shared DTO/contract types rather than
  hand-duplicating a backend response shape in a feature's `types.ts`. If
  no shared contracts source exists yet, flag it rather than silently
  hand-typing — see `ARCHITECTURE.md` Part 2, rule 7.
